headlines.description: — P.J. Washington had 19 points and nine rebounds and the Charlotte Hornets avenged an earlier loss to Indiana with a 108-105 win over the Pacers on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Hornets bounce back, split two-game set with Pacers 108-105

headlines.description: — Atlanta held NBA scoring leader Bradley Beal to a season low in points, and Trae Young’s 41 helped the Hawks top the Wizards 116-100 Friday night in a game that saw Rajon Rondo, Russell Westbrook and Robin Lopez all get ejected.
headlines.shortLinkText: Young's 41 points in 3-ejection game help Hawks beat Wizards

events.name: Cleveland Cavaliers at New York Knicks

headlines.description: — Rookie guard Immanuel Quickley scored 25 points off the bench, leading the New York Knicks to a 102-81 win over the Cleveland Cavaliers on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Knicks snap 3-game losing streak with 102-81 rout of Cavs

headlines.description: — Harrison Barnes scored 26 points, De'Aaron Fox added 24 and the Sacramento Kings beat the Toronto Raptors 126-124 on Friday night for their third straight victory.
headlines.shortLinkText: Kings hold off Raptors 126-124 for third straight win

events.name: Milwaukee Bucks at New Orleans Pelicans

headlines.description: — Lonzo Ball highlighted a season-best 27-point performance with seven 3-pointers and the New Orleans Pelicans held off a furious Milwaukee rally to beat the Bucks 131-126 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Ingram, Ball lead Pelicans past Bucks, 131-126

headlines.description: — Paul George had 26 points, nine rebounds and five assists, Kawhi Leonard added 24 points and the Los Angeles Clippers routed the Orlando Magic 116-90 on Friday night in the two All-Stars’ returns following two-game absences because of COVID-19...
headlines.shortLinkText: Leonard, George stellar in returns as Clippers thump Magic

headlines.description: — Joel Embiid racked up 37 points and 11 rebounds in 27 minutes, leading the Philadelphia 76ers to a 118-94 victory over the depleted Minnesota Timberwolves on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Embiid has 37 points as 76ers ease past Wolves, 118-94

events.name: Brooklyn Nets at Oklahoma City Thunder

headlines.description: — James Harden and Kyrie Irving each scored 25 points Friday night to help Brooklyn roll past the Oklahoma City Thunder 147-125, as the Nets rested Kevin Durant.
headlines.shortLinkText: Nets don't miss rested Durant in 147-125 win over Thunder

events.name: Denver Nuggets at San Antonio Spurs

headlines.description: — DeMar DeRozan had 30 points and 10 assists, Dejounte Murray scored 26 points and the San Antonio Spurs beat Denver 119-109 on Friday night to snap the Nuggets’ five-game winning streak.
headlines.shortLinkText: DeRozan leads Spurs to 119-109 win, ending Nuggets' streak

headlines.description: — Bojan Bogdanovic scored 17 of his season-high 32 points in the third quarter and the Utah Jazz completed a sweep of the Dallas Mavericks with a 120-101 victory on Friday night to run their NBA-best winning streak to 11.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jazz finish sweep of Mavericks 120-101 for 11th straight win
